  "prompt": "What is the most used word in Malayalam?",
  "response": "Identifying the most used word in Malayalam is challenging as it depends heavily on context, such as conversational settings, literature, media, or specific topics. However, common words in everyday conversation often include connectors and functional words. These include \"\u0d06\u0d23\u0d4d\" (aanu, meaning \"is\"), \"\u0d06\u0d30\u0d41\u0d02\" (aaru, meaning \"who\"), \"\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46\" (ente, meaning \"my\"), and \"\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d46\" (enne, meaning \"me\"). Quantifying the most frequently used word across all contexts would require a comprehensive analysis of Malayalam text data.",
